    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "MILAN, May 17 (Reuters) - Italy’s talismanic goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon will play his last match for Juventus when they host Verona in Serie A on Saturday, he told reporters on Thursday, according to Italian media.\n“Saturday will be my last game for Juventus. I think it’s the best way to end this wonderful adventure,” the 40-year-old said. Buffon has been at Juventus since 2001. (Writing by Brian Homewood in Bern; Editing by Kevin Liffey)\n ",
